# Java 17 Migration Summary

## Overview
Successfully migrated the java-ui-factory project from Java 8 to Java 17.

## Changes Made

### 1. POM.xml Updates

#### Maven Compiler Configuration
- Updated `maven-compiler-plugin` from version 2.3 to 3.11.0
- Configured source, target, and release to Java 17
- Removed obsolete `compilerVersion` parameter

#### Plugin Version Updates
- `maven-compiler-plugin`: 2.3 → 3.11.0
- `maven-checkstyle-plugin`: 2.6 → 3.3.1
- `maven-javadoc-plugin`: 2.9.1 → 3.6.3
- `maven-source-plugin`: 2.2.1 → 3.3.0
- `maven-release-plugin`: 2.5 → 3.0.1
- `maven-gpg-plugin`: 1.5 → 3.1.0
- `nexus-staging-maven-plugin`: 1.6.3 → 1.6.13

#### New Dependencies Added
Added JAXB dependencies (removed from JDK in Java 11+):
- `jakarta.xml.bind:jakarta.xml.bind-api:4.0.2`
- `com.sun.xml.bind:jaxb-impl:4.0.5` (runtime scope)

### 2. Source Code Changes

#### Package Name Updates
Updated 15 Java source files to use the new Jakarta EE namespace:
- Changed `import javax.xml.bind.*` to `import jakarta.xml.bind.*`

Files affected:
- ComponentInfo.java
- TreeInfo.java
- MenuItemInfo.java
- MenuInfo.java
- MenuBarInfo.java
- ToolbarInfo.java
- ToolbarItemInfo.java
- ComboBoxInfo.java
- ComboBoxItemInfo.java
- ListInfo.java
- ListItemInfo.java
- JComboBoxFactory.java
- JToolBarFactory.java
- JListFactory.java

### 3. Build Verification

✅ **Build Status**: SUCCESS
- All compilation passes with Java 17
- All tests pass (3/3 tests passing)
- JAR files generated successfully:
  - Main JAR: java-ui-factory-core-0.5-SNAPSHOT.jar (172KB)

  - Javadoc JAR: java-ui-factory-core-0.5-SNAPSHOT-javadoc.jar (910KB)
- Bytecode verified at Java 17 level (major version 61)

## Key Migration Points

### JAXB Removal from JDK
The most significant change was handling the removal of JAXB from the JDK:
- JAXB was part of Java SE until Java 8
- Removed in Java 11 as part of modularization
- Now requires explicit dependencies
- Package namespace changed from `javax.xml.bind` to `jakarta.xml.bind`

### Maven Plugin Compatibility
Updated all Maven plugins to versions compatible with Java 17:
- Older plugin versions don't recognize the `release` parameter
- Maven Javadoc Plugin 2.x doesn't work with Java 17

- Executed `mvn clean verify` successfully
- All unit tests pass
- No compilation errors or warnings (except for expected deprecation and unchecked operation warnings from existing code)
